<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-061-580  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 061 580.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  Jan 15 1990 v24 n3 p101(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Prisoners nab payroll password. (computer fraud at Tennessee StatePrison)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Pastore, Richard.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>As many as 18 inmates working as data-entry operators at TennesseeState Prison gave themselves unauthorized pay after gaining accessto the prison's computerized payroll system.andP;  The inmates, who arepaid 10 cents per 1,000 keystrokes, allegedly inflated theirkeystroke tallies to gain extra Dec 1989 pay ranging from $20 to$500 apiece.andP;  Authorities learned about the scam when acomputerized audit red-flagged unusually high keystroke totals.andO;Prison official Tom Mathis defends the program, saying theprisoner's lessons in work skills and ethics outweigh the risk forfraud and pointing out that prisons are not the only places wherecomputer fraud takes place.andP;  The prisoners face legal action ifthey do not return their ill-gotten booty.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     TennesseeComputer CrimesAccess RightsPayroll.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>